  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\n\n2.14.1\n\n### What happened?\n\nIn a project with both solidity and vyper compilers configured, when trying to verify a deployed Vyper contract on Arbitrum, hardhat tries to match it to a solidity compiler version and fails.\r\n\r\n```\r\n// hardhat.config.js \r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n    solidity: {\r\n        compilers: [\r\n          {\r\n            version: \"0.7.6\",\r\n          },\r\n          {\r\n            version: \"0.8.20\",\r\n          },\r\n        ],\r\n    },\r\n\r\n    vyper: {\r\n        compilers: [\r\n            {\r\n                version: \"0.3.9\",\r\n            },\r\n            {\r\n                version: \"0.3.7\"\r\n            }\r\n        ]\r\n    },\r\n```\r\n\r\nError message:\r\n```\r\nCompilerVersionsMismatchError: The contract you want to verify was compiled with solidity 0.4.7 - 0.5.8, but your configured compiler versions are: 0.7.6, 0.8.20.\r\n```\r\n\r\n\n\n### Minimal reproduction steps\n\nUse provided hardhat config, deploy a Vyper 0.3.7 contract to Arbitrum, run\r\n\r\n```\r\nnpx hardhat verify —network arbitrum DEPLOYED_CONTRACT_ADDRESS\r\n```\r\n\r\n\n\n### Search terms\n\nHardhat verify vyper solidity compiler mismatch",
